# Core Rules

- Read and follow AI_RULES.md before proposing code changes.
- Make the smallest correct change.
- Do not modify unrelated files.
- Do not introduce new abstractions unless they clearly remove duplication across multiple real usages.
- Prefer explicit code over magic.
- If a task implies architecture changes, explain the impact before editing.
- Never generate placeholder code, fake implementations, or TODO-only stubs unless explicitly requested.
